[
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.1",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Praise ye the LORD. O give thanks unto the LORD; for {he is} good: for his mercy {endureth} for ever. {Praise...: Heb. Hallelujah}",
    "hash": "89cb147c43baf6ba02529299578ba6541463c18ffbbb19a9ac777e1d0bfb04b7"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.2",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Who can utter the mighty acts of the LORD? {who} can shew forth all his praise?",
    "hash": "e54e540feb2ca79d90ac9eeac3fe1a77db1a796521b1b15ee2aee0d3350df334"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.3",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Blessed {are} they that keep judgment, {and} he that doeth righteousness at all times.",
    "hash": "c0a1bf9502bd33abca431a045875de2f5d884ebc4709a699062bc2000a121a59"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.4",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Remember me, O LORD, with the favour {that thou bearest unto} thy people: O visit me with thy salvation;",
    "hash": "d270397658066b8c46569f60ad14d2393e4929ac15d0c367165ebd4cf97f7713"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.5",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "That I may see the good of thy chosen, that I may rejoice in the gladness of thy nation, that I may glory with thine inheritance.",
    "hash": "e19fe31b3dfa8c1a3cc6b22f175119146082e4d48e0a8f0532594b1875ae2044"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.6",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "We have sinned with our fathers, we have committed iniquity, we have done wickedly.",
    "hash": "4bbcc5693a457f1ea0d85efb1ba61ca8122228f2bf15e2158b0fbc54b57c94dc"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.7",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Our fathers understood not thy wonders in Egypt; they remembered not the multitude of thy mercies; but provoked {him} at the sea, {even} at the Red sea.",
    "hash": "929235324a1ac11212872e4ba94a41386cf5ad1ed9b9847c6b3347f3a1c2b982"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.8",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Nevertheless he saved them for his name's sake, that he might make his mighty power to be known.",
    "hash": "b29615cd523204e55f17790a86c25d543541dbbd8d5dd2a000ad84f469506d4a"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.9",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "He rebuked the Red sea also, and it was dried up: so he led them through the depths, as through the wilderness.",
    "hash": "fb5639fbfc88f1e5f0bc715ea54bb01883ee25d442c3597f516debdada359029"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.10",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "And he saved them from the hand of him that hated {them}, and redeemed them from the hand of the enemy.",
    "hash": "ad29a0237f9141b29a79265ecd15217a74ec77fa54ccabbc7715e070b7c35c0a"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.11",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "And the waters covered their enemies: there was not one of them left.",
    "hash": "ea2b5b6a5bb01fff95843370ae3eae46468a07fee84d1f2db51adb72432be0b9"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.12",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Then believed they his words; they sang his praise.",
    "hash": "f9464de62c1bc0af395e961aa5da4db0a68c16c02877329a3439a9d985bf067f"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.13",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "They soon forgat his works; they waited not for his counsel: {They soon...: Heb. They made haste, they forgat}",
    "hash": "d4457799e79512ea8d2eff28cb2bdd95eba13d16a12e5ca61211e914f2494657"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.14",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "But lusted exceedingly in the wilderness, and tempted God in the desert. {lusted...: Heb. lusted a lust}",
    "hash": "86de9cd2d288748e3ab4e0c1841a72230e7a21affd8b4d17da9e36395a724764"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.15",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "And he gave them their request; but sent leanness into their soul.",
    "hash": "45a076a23ecc9fcb79a5dfd5699da152efa6b0fb0acdc4f266a383bc406557ed"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.16",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "They envied Moses also in the camp, {and} Aaron the saint of the LORD.",
    "hash": "42c834a73b87fab8b114e194e505c0a0ceecf5c0809efe4d21cd7ab274a78aeb"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.17",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "The earth opened and swallowed up Dathan, and covered the company of Abiram.",
    "hash": "bca1f632f41cdfc140e62b2d452654caf7a34b449574aa26c88f6c771429a0f6"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.18",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "And a fire was kindled in their company; the flame burned up the wicked.",
    "hash": "d0d91fe8580d3f68407a3fbc332273d18c28ed6079db9ff4f370a7b4d0f4e460"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.19",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "They made a calf in Horeb, and worshipped the molten image.",
    "hash": "364ae080c91aaab497fbf106bffde76c20c6e2b897471472c642eb53bb903f23"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.20",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Thus they changed their glory into the similitude of an ox that eateth grass.",
    "hash": "a5b588a4734d4f0c8c4524549c1981ed76e41070ee5590a47201f53b10398422"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.21",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "They forgat God their saviour, which had done great things in Egypt;",
    "hash": "20fddb471867c7b8594fdf9cd7f6305c24d67bb77677f96275f16a901ba7618c"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.22",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "Wondrous works in the land of Ham, {and} terrible things by the Red sea.",
    "hash": "1d2906200c5588f910b0502f1656b3548ce6484a4b8f6a3ad2d25ce602ce6b40"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.23",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "Therefore he said that he would destroy them, had not Moses his chosen stood before him in the breach, to turn away his wrath, lest he should destroy {them}.",
    "hash": "8522a45362a26babf378d93e3490ea466d468766c3f2ab32e884d6e987995281"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.24",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "Yea, they despised the pleasant land, they believed not his word: {the pleasant...: Heb. a land of desire}",
    "hash": "6e1cf8c799ec975bcca296ea994c31033b26b3e9427407602634f4e2fa591cb5"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.25",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "But murmured in their tents, {and} hearkened not unto the voice of the LORD.",
    "hash": "664065cb006e20bbc3664ab1279d42da454b6e91da735ae135a6b30473c92e9e"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.26",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "Therefore he lifted up his hand against them, to overthrow them in the wilderness: {to overthrow: Heb. to make them fall}",
    "hash": "0f79c074831985fda4988fb587390e97bafd3540018312ef2eb0a49dd8c85825"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.27",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "To overthrow their seed also among the nations, and to scatter them in the lands. {to overthrow: Heb. to make them fall}",
    "hash": "657d64039aa48f1a50b543f3e0c854d6436fba734ffc02536117295489988e6a"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.28",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "They joined themselves also unto Baalpeor, and ate the sacrifices of the dead.",
    "hash": "4e765973f3e80043c01590d2b2967761281dc5abfdfd076d3a9a140b7747ea70"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.29",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "Thus they provoked {him} to anger with their inventions: and the plague brake in upon them.",
    "hash": "b0ced67efed7004e45e7ba60e69f6d81860e9b60adcb6e0be316562a4a6195ba"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.30",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "Then stood up Phinehas, and executed judgment: and {so} the plague was stayed.",
    "hash": "310dea2cd6eab2d402c06f260bd2a70d2408385009a6141135f0d086880e78a6"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.31",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "And that was counted unto him for righteousness unto all generations for evermore.",
    "hash": "d684a8420945902606a91cffd324c047e765c53db38e8a1e43db646ccbfa0471"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.32",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "They angered {him} also at the waters of strife, so that it went ill with Moses for their sakes:",
    "hash": "1feee34a83de4ab144f555edc3971e1d53049e88291f5ebd98d8bf61f99d6985"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.33",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "Because they provoked his spirit, so that he spake unadvisedly with his lips.",
    "hash": "22f771ad3df1580dc30798f93b91f8601eb72e2ecc39a4da21ded4cd7933d44f"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.34",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "They did not destroy the nations, concerning whom the LORD commanded them:",
    "hash": "91f26401755973437ecfdc53730236f1b95d5d37a30c002a5cbe0c5f627ad5f9"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.35",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "But were mingled among the heathen, and learned their works.",
    "hash": "9c82fdd1f8b0498b16dc196020254bdb1da292b87e3415f9b7465f8a57d64bcf"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.36",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 36,
    "text": "And they served their idols: which were a snare unto them.",
    "hash": "eb3545e78c12e604a5f91cb6c9c8ca91741eb12e71a657ffe33d229f7f75e45d"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.37",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 37,
    "text": "Yea, they sacrificed their sons and their daughters unto devils,",
    "hash": "30bf585b7583a8b7c57a5e3bc2d60459941b972c8a37b04747c850b98c64d2cf"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.38",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 38,
    "text": "And shed innocent blood, {even} the blood of their sons and of their daughters, whom they sacrificed unto the idols of Canaan: and the land was polluted with blood.",
    "hash": "beeb144e9ade839a9c3424e6f6840b35c227a3f412dd609850a55ea376103911"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.39",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 39,
    "text": "Thus were they defiled with their own works, and went a whoring with their own inventions.",
    "hash": "eea83082fafa29c309d76f833c77a8b6cf8d07842726e92b099e4cc9b1ee1c01"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.40",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 40,
    "text": "Therefore was the wrath of the LORD kindled against his people, insomuch that he abhorred his own inheritance.",
    "hash": "085b82fb4c54a883a0630970d56a7b7d5c64bb4f5af3fda4a4b44423a469c68e"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.41",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 41,
    "text": "And he gave them into the hand of the heathen; and they that hated them ruled over them.",
    "hash": "d42154fd52b269b48fa8a24b305fdba0622b99e762ac9a9eff19b13ea47d9cd9"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.42",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 42,
    "text": "Their enemies also oppressed them, and they were brought into subjection under their hand.",
    "hash": "7518ca11952c506b6dc13f1d9563f57841ee08fcb9504d230275738cc80249c1"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.43",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 43,
    "text": "Many times did he deliver them; but they provoked {him} with their counsel, and were brought low for their iniquity. {brought...: or, impoverished, or, weakened}",
    "hash": "9c079e44ddd0e10fb4ecec593a092ec61dfa88a4bc1e9094aabaa418d8ece4a3"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.44",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 44,
    "text": "Nevertheless he regarded their affliction, when he heard their cry:",
    "hash": "3702943807eaefbf078026fc7c45e0630899a5dbd63b1fb8e021074e3069155a"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.45",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 45,
    "text": "And he remembered for them his covenant, and repented according to the multitude of his mercies.",
    "hash": "5707cd9bffe674fd0124ec5a024c72fc2583a6b9d643dbf7674665486745852c"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.46",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 46,
    "text": "He made them also to be pitied of all those that carried them captives.",
    "hash": "46133d02ea71b882d87a9dbb0a5d551caf5fa42c1ba8a37568de33d7d198e60d"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.47",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 47,
    "text": "Save us, O LORD our God, and gather us from among the heathen, to give thanks unto thy holy name, {and} to triumph in thy praise.",
    "hash": "d39299f80102a10b969837602e00f7998634b8527c50c1b8e14dc547ae7df135"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.106.48",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 106,
    "verse": 48,
    "text": "Blessed {be} the LORD God of Israel from everlasting to everlasting: and let all the people say, Amen. Praise ye the LORD. {Praise...: Heb. Hallelujah}",
    "hash": "2584555e1abd570bec8295748f804355ae64c22469dc7b6c6eb8ecf130fd3848"
  }
]